y\n|Independent \n|\"Debt\"\n|Nevers Road\n|featured vocal\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2020\n|[[Jason Ross (musician)|Jason Ross]]\n|Ophelia\n|\"1000 Faces\"\n\"Someone That I Needed\"\n| 1000 Faces\n|co-writer, featured vocal\n|-\n|William Black, Fairlane\n|Lowly\n|\"Butterflies\"\n|N/A\n|co-writer, featured vocal\n|-\n|Nurko\n|Proximity\n|\"Faith\"\n|N/A\n|co-writer, featured vocal\n|}\n\n==Videography==\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=10 | Year\n! width=150 | Title\n! width=100 | Director\n|-\n| 2011 || \"The Broken Ones\" || David McClister\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2013 || \"Over It\" <br><small>(with [[The Crystal Method]])</small>|| Zak Stoltz\n|-\n| \"Stubborn Love\" <br><small>(with [[The Lumineers]])</small>|| Issac Ravishankara\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2017 || \"Don't Look Back\"|| Michael Kaminsky, Braverijah Gregg and Eric Tobin\n|-\n| \"Dead Man\"|| Andrew Ahn\n|-\n|\"Crave\"\n|Andrew Ahn\n|}\n\n===Filmography===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2015\n|Blank Pages\n|Roosevelt\n|2 episodes\n|-\n|2016\n|The Crooked Man\n|Mia\n|TV Movie\n|-\n|2017\n|Criminal Minds\n|Jillian Flanagan\n|Season 12 episode 11\n|-\n|2018\n|Maybe I'm Fine\n|Maya\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|[[I Ship It]]\n|Amber the fangirl\n|Episode \"Superfans\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web|url=https://medium.com/cuepoint/id-get-to-the-top-of-the-mountain-if-it-would-just-stop-fucking-growing-252af2a6504b|last=Frampton|first=Dia|title=I'd Get to the Top of the Mountain if It Would Just Stop Fucking Growing|work=Cuepoint|publisher=Medium|date=August 30, 2016|accessdate=September 2, 2016}}\n\n{{The Voice (U.S.)}}\n{{Meg & Dia}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Frampton, Dia}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American people of Dutch descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American women of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Guitarists from Utah]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Salt Lake City]]\n[[Category:People from St. George, Utah]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from Utah]]\n[[Category:The Voice (franchise) contestants]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:Nettwerk Music Group artists]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toJason Ross(link changed toJason Ross (musician)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dia_Frampton"}
{"title_page": "Max Maven", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Max Maven\n| image              = Max Maven.jpg\n| alt                = Max Maven performing an ESP card trick, 2007\n| caption            = Maven performing an ESP card trick, 2007\n| birth_name         = Philip Goldstein\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1950|12|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Ithaca, New York]]\n| residence          = [[Hollywood, California]]\n| occupation         = [[Magic (illusion)|Magician]], [[mentalist]]\n| awards             = Academy of Magical Arts Creative Fellowship, MINDVention Lifetime Achievement Award,The Allan Slaight Award for Lifetime Achievement\n}}\n\n'''Max Maven''' (born '''Philip Goldstein''', 21 December 1950) is an [[United States|American]] [[Magic (illusion)|magician]] and [[mentalist]] whose performances are considered erudite and intelligent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laweekly.com/max-maven-thinking-in-person/|title=Max Maven Thinking in Person|last=Morris|first=Steven Leigh|date=2008-03-27|website=LA Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> He is ranked as one of the most influential mentalists of all time,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://magiciansmag.com/mentalism/10-famous-mentalists-of-all-time/|title=10 Famous Mentalists of all Time.|last=magicianmagazineonline|date=2017-03-31|website=Magicians Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and one of the 100 \"Most Influential Magicians of the 20th Century\" by ''[[Magic magazine|Magic Magazine]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stevensmagic.com/2009/maven/|title=Maven|date=2009-08-01|website=Stevens Magic Emporium|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://comedycontact.com/max-maven/|title=Max Maven \u2013 Comedy Contact. We make finding the right entertainer easy.|date=2014-10-14|website=Comedy Contact.  We make finding the right entertainer easy.|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe often appears on television magic shows to perform \"interactive\" mind reading tricks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GdEuf2YJ2SEC&pg=PP28&lpg=PP28&dq=max+maven+interactive+magic+tricks&source=bl&ots=Lsd58bgDyq&sig=ACfU3U2gk6SYHnOUNo46xOqMPvbZ80r0YQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiR8Nej9JLkAhUDqp4KHbnoCLYQ6AEwD3oECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=max%20maven%20interactive%20magic%20tricks&f=false|title=Max Maven Interactive Magic Tricks|website=Google Books|access-date=August 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/picks-and-pans-review-max-mavens-mindgames-vol-22-no-19/|title=Picks and Pans Review: Max Maven's Mindgames|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> Among other cities, including [[Rome]], Maven grew up largely in [[Boston]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rebelmagic.com/max-maven-spotlight/|title=Max Maven: A Mentalist, Magic Consultant, And A TV Guest Star|website=Rebel Magic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> [[Massachusetts]], where he became known for his performances at several nightspots including the then popular [[Playboy Club]]. In Boston, he was formerly a radio deejay.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-06-24-ca-8136-story.html|title=Insight From Maven of the Mind : Stage: The mentalist, who will perform in Santa Ana, says he gets hints from body language.|date=1994-06-24|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe is a prolific author<ref>{{cite journal\n  | title = Obituaries (Mike Caldwell)\n  | journal = Genii\n  | volume = 58\n  | issue = 10 \n  | pages = 858\n  | publisher = William W. Larsen Corporation\n  | date= September 1995\n   }}\n</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.librarything.com/author/mavenmax|title=Max Maven|website=www.librarything.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and conceived many magical and mentalist effects used by other magicians<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/off-broadway/article/Photo-Flash-Max-Maven-Celebrates-Opening-Night-Off-Broadway-20120615|title=Photo Flash: Max Maven Celebrates Opening Night Off-Broadway|last=Desk|first=BWW News|website=BroadwayWorld.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. He has been a [[magic consultant]] for such performers as [[David Copperfield (illusionist)|David Copperfield]] and [[Penn & Teller]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/07/05/arts/new-magic-makes-the-audience-appear.html|title=New Magic Makes the Audience Appear|last=Collins|first=Glenn|date=1987-07-05|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-08-21|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>, [[Siegfried & Roy]], and [[Doug Henning]], and is a frequent contributor to industry journals such as ''[[Genii (magazine)|Genii]],'' ''[[The Linking Ring]]'', and ''[[M-U-M]]'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.conjuringarchive.com/list/person/1607?withpennames=on&page=2|title=Max Maven|website=www.conjuringarchive.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>.\n\nHe has been featured on the cover of over 30 such magazines over the years<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://amazingshows.com/event/max-maven/|title=Max Maven - World's Top Mentalist (2018-09-06)|last=Dreams|first=Theatre of|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, including ''The Linking Ring, Genii'' in 1983<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://geniimagazine.com/wiki/index.php?title=Shigeo_Takagi|title=Shigeo Takagi - Magicpedia|website=geniimagazine.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> (with Japanese magician [[Shigeo Takagi]]), and also in 2007<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://geniimagazine.com/wiki/index.php?title=Max_Maven|title=Max Maven - Magicpedia|website=geniimagazine.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and in 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.penguinmagic.com/p/S24525|title=Genii Magazine February 2018 - Book|website=Penguin Magic|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, and on the cover of ''Penguin Magic Monthly'' in 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.penguinmagic.com/p/11416|title=Penguin Magic Monthly: January 2019 (Magazine)|website=Penguin Magic|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. He has also been the featured magician at the annual conventions of both the [[Society of American Magicians]] and the [[International Brotherhood of Magicians]].\n\nHis name has been changed legally to Max Maven but he still uses \"Phil Goldstein\" as a pen name for technical writings.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mekGtpHh5zUC&pg=PT57&lpg=PT57&dq=max+maven+legal+name+change&source=bl&ots=p9kfjyg5Rs&sig=ACfU3U2giX8vNoZGdsBj_S3FbCXGxwNd2w&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjP857r8pLkAhV6HDQIHU3tCx8Q6AEwB3oECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=max%20maven%20legal%20name%20change&f=false|title=Mind Magic and Mentalism For Dummies|last=Clark|first=James L.|date=2012-03-27|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=9781119954002|language=en}}</ref>\n\nMaven is considered a legend in the world of magic<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jewishjournal.com/newspulse/97484/|title=Magician Max Maven Reads My Mind [VIDEO]|last=href='https://jewishjournal.com/author/'></a>|first=BY <a|date=2011-10-26|website=Jewish Journal|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stevensmagic.com/2009/maven/|title=Maven|date=2009-08-01|website=Stevens Magic Emporium|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, and has a broad knowledge of magic history and the origins various tricks and methods.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RR3SK3Md8WsC&pg=PA272&lpg=PA272&dq=max+maven+expert&source=bl&ots=4Vz2Us_0dv&sig=ACfU3U2TsRunMUWd3q0wzNrxkE_KhoY5GA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwijpK-xjZPkAhVrHDQIHUtRBXs4ChDoATADegQICBAB#v=onepage&q=max%20maven%20expert&f=false|title=Joshua Jay Book of Magic|authorlink=Joshua Jay|website=books.google.com|publisher=Workman|access-date=August 20, 2019}}</ref> He has stated that he believes it vital to preserve the history of the art and provide credit to the originators of ideas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rebelmagic.com/max-maven-spotlight/|title=Max Maven: A Mentalist, Magic Consultant, And A TV Guest Star|website=Rebel Magic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n== Media and Public Appearances ==\nAlthough he doesn't consider himself a comedian,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ocweekly.com/magician-or-mentalist-max-maven-is-mentally-amazing-6586251/|title=Magician or Mentalist, Max Maven is Mentally Amazing|last=Lerman|first=Ali|date=2011-10-24|website=OC Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> Max Maven spent much of the 1980s performing and headlining in comedy clubs throughout the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://talkingtricks.podbean.com/e/max-maven/|title=MAX MAVEN|last=Development|first=PodBean|website=talkingtricks.podbean.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mspentertainmentagency.com/maxmaven|title=Max Maven - Entertainment Booking Agency|website=mspentertainmentagency.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bermudasun.bm/Content/LIFESTYLE/Lifestyle/Article/Bringing-mystery-back-to-life/9/230/32412|title=Bringing mystery back to life|date=February 2, 2007|website=bermudasun.bm|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHis one man show, ''Thinking in Person'', ran for two months at the [[Beverly Hills Playhouse]] in 1988<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-06-24-ca-8136-story.html|title=Insight From Maven of the Mind : Stage: The mentalist, who will perform in Santa Ana, says he gets hints from body language.|date=1994-06-24|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, and an expanded version of the show was relaunched twenty years later in 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laweekly.com/max-maven-thinking-in-person/|title=Max Maven Thinking in Person|last=Morris|first=Steven Leigh|date=2008-03-27|website=LA Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. The show was later mounted Off-Broadway at the Abingdon Theatre Arts Complex in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/mentalist-max-mavens-thinking-in-person-begins-off-broadway-run-june-12-com-194543|title=Mentalist Max Maven's Thinking in Person Begins Off-Broadway Run June 12|last=Gioia|first=Michael|date=June 12, 2012|website=Playbill|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe has occasionally played a magician character (often as himself) on various television series, such as, \"Magic\", \"The Art of Magic\", \"Something Strange with Max Maven\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Something Strange with Max Maven|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0227951/|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, and \"The MAXimum Dimension\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxmaven.com/MAXimum.php|title=MAXimum Dimension|accessdate=31 October 2011}}</ref> He has appeared in television series in Sweden, Norway, Finland, Taiwan, England, Canada, Spain, Portugal, and Chile.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sleightsofmind.com/|title=Sleights of Mind \u00bb Magic Advisors|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mspentertainmentagency.com/maxmaven|title=Max Maven - Entertainment Booking Agency|website=mspentertainmentagency.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nMaven has appeared as a part of the traveling science exhibit called \"Magic: The Science of Illusion\" and the \"Magic of the Mind Illusion,\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.maxmaven.com/max.php|title=All About Max ~ MaxMaven.com|website=www.maxmaven.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> which has toured in science museums such as Los Angeles and Boston.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.magicexhibit.org/illusions/illusions_MM.html|title=Magic:The Science of Illusion|accessdate=31 October 2011}}</ref> He has performed often in [[Japan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themagiccafe.com/forums/viewtopic.php?topic=114373&forum=160|title=Magic Cafe|accessdate=31 October 2011}}</ref> and speaks Japanese.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-06-24-ca-8136-story.html|title=Insight From Maven of the Mind : Stage: The mentalist, who will perform in Santa Ana, says he gets hints from body language.|date=1994-06-24|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe has been a frequent speaker at the [[EG Conference]] on creativity and innovation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.egconf.com/presenters/max-maven|title=Max Maven|date=2014-04-07|website=EG Conference|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.egconf.com/videos/max-maven-mystery-theorist-magician-eg8|title=Max Maven, Mystery Theorist & Magician (EG8)|date=2015-11-06|website=EG Conference|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe hosted a 12-part series for [[ITV Wales & West|HTV (Harlech Television)]] in Britain, \"Something Strange with Max Maven,\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Something Strange with Max Maven|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0227951/|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> a talk-show exploring all aspects of the paranormal. The show set a ratings record, and led to a second series the following year. He also starred as the title role in [[Fox Broadcasting Company|FOX]]'s 1992 Halloween special ''Count DeClues' Mystery Castle''<ref>{{Citation|title=Count DeClues' Mystery Castle|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0770733/|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. His performed his interactive magic on [[The World's Greatest Magic]], NBC's highest rated special of 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mspentertainmentagency.com/maxmaven|title=Max Maven - Entertainment Booking Agency|website=mspentertainmentagency.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> \n\nHe hosted his own show on [[Israel]]'s [[Channel 2 (Israeli TV channel)|Channel 2]], a licensed version of ''[[Penn & Teller: Fool Us]]'' called ''Mi Yapil Et Ha Master'' (\"Who Can Fool The Master?)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://itricks.com/news/2017/06/max-maven-fool-me/|title=iTricks.com Magic News, Magic Videos and Podcasts \u00bb Blog Archive \u00bb Max Maven: Fool Me?|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. And he was a judge for a number of episodes of the 2008 TV [[reality tv]] series [[Celebracadabra]]. <ref>{{Citation|title=Celebracadabra|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1173669/|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe appeared in [[Sitcom]]<nowiki/>s and TV dramas, including as \"The Great Mentos\" in the 1995 [[Fresh Prince of Bel Air]] episode \"Save the Last Trance for Me,\" the 1982 episode of [[Mork & Mindy]] entitled \"Drive, She Said,\" and episodes of [[General Hospital]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0561364/|title=Max Maven|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.belenzon.com/talent/max-maven/|title=Max Maven - David Belenzon Management, Inc - Max Maven|website=David Belenzon Management, Inc.|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and [[Top Chef]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2009/07/09/top-chef-masters-neil-patrick-harris/|title='Top Chef Masters': Neil Patrick Harris masters another TV genre|website=EW.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2019, he appeared on screen in the documentary about [[The Amazing Johnathan]] directed by Ben Berman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/movies/story/2019-08-14/amazing-johnathan-documentary-magic|title=Review: \u2018The Amazing Johnathan Documentary\u2019 profiles irascible magician in an illusory way|date=2019-08-15|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and was interviewed<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/food/story/2019-07-24/magic-castle-hollywood-new-chef|title=And for the Magic Castle's next trick: Food that\u2019s worth talking about|date=2019-07-25|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> by the [[Los Angeles Times]] about recent developments at [[The Magic Castle]]. \n\nThe well-reviewed<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://magicreviewed.com/reviews/donna-zuckerbrot-max-maven-a-fabulous-monster/|title=Donna Zuckerbrot-Max Maven - A Fabulous Monster|website=Magic Reviewed|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> feature documentary entitled ''Max Maven: A Fabulous Monster'' was released about him in 2007<ref>{{Citation|title=Max Maven: A Fabulous Monster|url=https://www.gaia.com/video/max-maven-fabulous-monster|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> by Reel Time Images. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.reeltimeimages.ca/project/max-maven-a-fabulous-monster/|title=Max Maven: A Fabulous Monster|access-date=August 20, 2019}}</ref> It is available for streaming on Amazon Prime.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Max-Maven-Fabulous-Colm-Feore/dp/B00NTSN8VI|title=Amazon.com: Watch Max Maven: A Fabulous Monster {{!}} Prime Video|website=www.amazon.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and Recognitions ==\nMax Maven has received a number of awards for his creativity and performance, including awards from the [[Society of American Magicians]], [[International Brotherhood of Magicians]], and the [[Academy of Magical Arts]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GdEuf2YJ2SEC&pg=PP28&lpg=PP28&dq=max+maven+awards&source=bl&ots=Lsd58bjBuo&sig=ACfU3U0rzNz5cf0NGWgajTiCzBacDtPv9w&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjAyvHG_pLkAhWXqZ4KHfbRDwI4ChDoATAHegQICRAB#v=onepage&q=max%20maven%20awards&f=false|title=Max Maven, Technical Reviewer|website=books.google.com|access-date=August 20, 2019}}</ref> In addition, he has received the following recognitions:\n\n*[[Academy of Magical Arts]] Lecturer of the Year, 1979{{cn|date=August 2019}}\n*[[Academy of Magical Arts]] Creative Fellowship, 1997{{cn|date=August 2019}}\n*The Magic Woods Award for Best Teaching Video for his mentalism DVD \"Nothing,\" 2007.<ref>{{cite journal|date=March 1981|title=Cover page (Special Max Maven issue)|journal=Genii|volume=45|issue=3|pages=1}}</ref>\n*MINDVention Lifetime Achievement Award, 2015<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themagiccafe.com/forums/viewtopic.php?topic=580200&forum=310|title=The Magic Cafe Forums - Max Maven 2015 Guest of Honor!|website=www.themagiccafe.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*The [[Allan Slaight]] Award for Lifetime Achievement, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.magicana.com/video/max-maven-bank-night|title=Max Maven Bank Night|date=2016-05-02|website=Magicana|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.magicana.com/allan-slaight-award-recipients|title=Allan Slaight Award Recipients|date=2016-06-27|website=Magicana|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n== Selected works ==\n* ''Max Maven's Book of Fortunetelling'' <ref>{{Cite book|title=Max Maven's book of fortunetelling|last=Maven|first=Max|date=1992|publisher=Prentice Hall General Reference|isbn=0135641217|edition=1st|location=New York|oclc=25632502}}</ref>\n* ''VideoMind - Phases 1-3: Mentalism'' (3 volume DVD)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://llpub.com/dvds-c-27/videomind-phase-1-parlor-mentalism-max-maven-dvd-p-1332.html|title=Videomind: Phase 1 - Parlor Mentalism - Max Maven - DVD [v2584] - $29.95 : L&L Publishing, The best in magic dvds, books, props and magician's supplies|website=llpub.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://llpub.com/dvds-c-27/videomind-closeup-mentalism-dvd-2-max-maven-p-1331.html|title=Videomind: Close-Up Mentalism - DVD # 2 - Max Maven [v2583] - $29.95 : L&L Publishing, The best in magic dvds, books, props and magician's supplies|website=llpub.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://llpub.com/dvds-c-27/videomind-stage-mentalism-dvd-3-max-maven-p-1333.html|title=Videomind: Stage Mentalism - DVD # 3 - Max Maven [v2585] - $29.95 : L&L Publishing, The best in magic dvds, books, props and magician's supplies|website=llpub.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*''Prism: The Color Series of Mentalism''<ref>{{Cite book|title=Prism: the color series of mentalism|last=Maven|first=Max|date=2005|publisher=Hermetic Press|isbn=0945296487|location=Seattle, WA|oclc=224853800}}</ref>\n*''Nothing'' (2 DVD Set) <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stevensmagic.global/product/nothing-by-max-maven-2-dvd-set/|title=Nothing by Max Maven (2 DVD Set)|website=Stevens Magic Global|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*''Kayfabe'' (4 DVD Set) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.penguinmagic.com/p/S24074|title=Kayfabe (4 DVD set) by Max Maven and Luis De Matos - DVD|website=Penguin Magic|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*''Max Maven's Mindgames'' (video)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vhscollector.com/movie/max-mavens-mindgames|title=Max Maven's Mindgames {{!}} VHSCollector.com|website=vhscollector.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*''The New Magic of Japan'' (translator)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanishingincmagic.com/blog/fully-booked-magic-of-japan/|title=Fully Booked {{!}} New Magic of Japan|website=www.vanishingincmagic.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{ reflist }}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|www.maxmaven.com}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=0561364|name=Max Maven}}\n*[https://pointofinquiry.org/2006/01/max_maven_magic_and_skepticism/ Interview with Max Maven]\n\n{{Academy of Magical Arts Lecturer of the Year}}\n{{Academy of Magical Arts Creative Fellowship}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maven, Max}}\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:American magicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mentalists]]\n[[Category:Magic consultants]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Max Maven\n| image              = Max Maven.jpg\n| alt                = Max Maven performing an ESP card trick, 2007\n| caption            = Maven performing an ESP card trick, 2007\n| birth_name         = Philip Goldstein\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1950|12|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Ithaca, New York]]\n| residence          = [[Hollywood, California]]\n| occupation         = [[Magic (illusion)|Magician]], [[mentalist]]\n| awards             = Academy of Magical Arts Creative Fellowship, MINDVention Lifetime Achievement Award,The Allan Slaight Award for Lifetime Achievement\n}}\n\n'''Max Maven''' (born '''Philip Goldstein''', 21 December 1950) is an [[United States|American]] [[Magic (illusion)|magician]] and [[mentalist]] whose performances are considered erudite and intelligent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laweekly.com/max-maven-thinking-in-person/|title=Max Maven Thinking in Person|last=Morris|first=Steven Leigh|date=2008-03-27|website=LA Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> He is ranked as one of the most influential mentalists of all time,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://magiciansmag.com/mentalism/10-famous-mentalists-of-all-time/|title=10 Famous Mentalists of all Time.|last=magicianmagazineonline|date=2017-03-31|website=Magicians Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and one of the 100 \"Most Influential Magicians of the 20th Century\" by ''[[Magic magazine|Magic Magazine]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stevensmagic.com/2009/maven/|title=Maven|date=2009-08-01|website=Stevens Magic Emporium|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://comedycontact.com/max-maven/|title=Max Maven \u2013 Comedy Contact. We make finding the right entertainer easy.|date=2014-10-14|website=Comedy Contact.  We make finding the right entertainer easy.|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe often appears on television magic shows to perform \"interactive\" mind reading tricks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GdEuf2YJ2SEC&pg=PP28&lpg=PP28&dq=max+maven+interactive+magic+tricks&source=bl&ots=Lsd58bgDyq&sig=ACfU3U2gk6SYHnOUNo46xOqMPvbZ80r0YQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiR8Nej9JLkAhUDqp4KHbnoCLYQ6AEwD3oECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=max%20maven%20interactive%20magic%20tricks&f=false|title=Max Maven Interactive Magic Tricks|website=Google Books|access-date=August 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/picks-and-pans-review-max-mavens-mindgames-vol-22-no-19/|title=Picks and Pans Review: Max Maven's Mindgames|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> Among other cities, including [[Rome]], Maven grew up largely in [[Boston]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rebelmagic.com/max-maven-spotlight/|title=Max Maven: A Mentalist, Magic Consultant, And A TV Guest Star|website=Rebel Magic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> [[Massachusetts]], where he became known for his performances at several nightspots including the then popular [[Playboy Club]]. In Boston, he was formerly a radio deejay.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-06-24-ca-8136-story.html|title=Insight From Maven of the Mind : Stage: The mentalist, who will perform in Santa Ana, says he gets hints from body language.|date=1994-06-24|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe is a prolific author<ref>{{cite journal\n  | title = Obituaries (Mike Caldwell)\n  | journal = Genii\n  | volume = 58\n  | issue = 10 \n  | pages = 858\n  | publisher = William W. Larsen Corporation\n  | date= September 1995\n   }}\n</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.librarything.com/author/mavenmax|title=Max Maven|website=www.librarything.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and conceived many magical and mentalist effects used by other magicians<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/off-broadway/article/Photo-Flash-Max-Maven-Celebrates-Opening-Night-Off-Broadway-20120615|title=Photo Flash: Max Maven Celebrates Opening Night Off-Broadway|last=Desk|first=BWW News|website=BroadwayWorld.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. He has been a [[magic consultant]] for such performers as [[David Copperfield (illusionist)|David Copperfield]] and [[Penn & Teller]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/07/05/arts/new-magic-makes-the-audience-appear.html|title=New Magic Makes the Audience Appear|last=Collins|first=Glenn|date=1987-07-05|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-08-21|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>, [[Siegfried & Roy]], and [[Doug Henning]], and is a frequent contributor to industry journals such as ''[[Genii (magazine)|Genii]],'' ''[[The Linking Ring]]'', and ''[[M-U-M]]'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.conjuringarchive.com/list/person/1607?withpennames=on&page=2|title=Max Maven|website=www.conjuringarchive.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>.\n\nHe has been featured on the cover of over 30 such magazines over the years<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://amazingshows.com/event/max-maven/|title=Max Maven - World's Top Mentalist (2018-09-06)|last=Dreams|first=Theatre of|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, including ''The Linking Ring, Genii'' in 1983<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://geniimagazine.com/wiki/index.php?title=Shigeo_Takagi|title=Shigeo Takagi - Magicpedia|website=geniimagazine.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> (with Japanese magician [[Shigeo Takagi), and also in 2007<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://geniimagazine.com/wiki/index.php?title=Max_Maven|title=Max Maven - Magicpedia|website=geniimagazine.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and in 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.penguinmagic.com/p/S24525|title=Genii Magazine February 2018 - Book|website=Penguin Magic|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, and on the cover of ''Penguin Magic Monthly'' in 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.penguinmagic.com/p/11416|title=Penguin Magic Monthly: January 2019 (Magazine)|website=Penguin Magic|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. He has also been the featured magician at the annual conventions of both the [[Society of American Magicians]] and the [[International Brotherhood of Magicians]].\n\nHis name has been changed legally to Max Maven but he still uses \"Phil Goldstein\" as a pen name for technical writings.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mekGtpHh5zUC&pg=PT57&lpg=PT57&dq=max+maven+legal+name+change&source=bl&ots=p9kfjyg5Rs&sig=ACfU3U2giX8vNoZGdsBj_S3FbCXGxwNd2w&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjP857r8pLkAhV6HDQIHU3tCx8Q6AEwB3oECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=max%20maven%20legal%20name%20change&f=false|title=Mind Magic and Mentalism For Dummies|last=Clark|first=James L.|date=2012-03-27|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=9781119954002|language=en}}</ref>\n\nMaven is considered a legend in the world of magic<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jewishjournal.com/newspulse/97484/|title=Magician Max Maven Reads My Mind [VIDEO]|last=href='https://jewishjournal.com/author/'></a>|first=BY <a|date=2011-10-26|website=Jewish Journal|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stevensmagic.com/2009/maven/|title=Maven|date=2009-08-01|website=Stevens Magic Emporium|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, and has a broad knowledge of magic history and the origins various tricks and methods.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RR3SK3Md8WsC&pg=PA272&lpg=PA272&dq=max+maven+expert&source=bl&ots=4Vz2Us_0dv&sig=ACfU3U2TsRunMUWd3q0wzNrxkE_KhoY5GA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwijpK-xjZPkAhVrHDQIHUtRBXs4ChDoATADegQICBAB#v=onepage&q=max%20maven%20expert&f=false|title=Joshua Jay Book of Magic|authorlink=Joshua Jay|website=books.google.com|publisher=Workman|access-date=August 20, 2019}}</ref> He has stated that he believes it vital to preserve the history of the art and provide credit to the originators of ideas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rebelmagic.com/max-maven-spotlight/|title=Max Maven: A Mentalist, Magic Consultant, And A TV Guest Star|website=Rebel Magic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n== Media and Public Appearances ==\nAlthough he doesn't consider himself a comedian,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ocweekly.com/magician-or-mentalist-max-maven-is-mentally-amazing-6586251/|title=Magician or Mentalist, Max Maven is Mentally Amazing|last=Lerman|first=Ali|date=2011-10-24|website=OC Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> Max Maven spent much of the 1980s performing and headlining in comedy clubs throughout the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://talkingtricks.podbean.com/e/max-maven/|title=MAX MAVEN|last=Development|first=PodBean|website=talkingtricks.podbean.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mspentertainmentagency.com/maxmaven|title=Max Maven - Entertainment Booking Agency|website=mspentertainmentagency.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bermudasun.bm/Content/LIFESTYLE/Lifestyle/Article/Bringing-mystery-back-to-life/9/230/32412|title=Bringing mystery back to life|date=February 2, 2007|website=bermudasun.bm|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHis one man show, ''Thinking in Person'', ran for two months at the [[Beverly Hills Playhouse]] in 1988<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-06-24-ca-8136-story.html|title=Insight From Maven of the Mind : Stage: The mentalist, who will perform in Santa Ana, says he gets hints from body language.|date=1994-06-24|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, and an expanded version of the show was relaunched twenty years later in 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.laweekly.com/max-maven-thinking-in-person/|title=Max Maven Thinking in Person|last=Morris|first=Steven Leigh|date=2008-03-27|website=LA Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. The show was later mounted Off-Broadway at the Abingdon Theatre Arts Complex in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/mentalist-max-mavens-thinking-in-person-begins-off-broadway-run-june-12-com-194543|title=Mentalist Max Maven's Thinking in Person Begins Off-Broadway Run June 12|last=Gioia|first=Michael|date=June 12, 2012|website=Playbill|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe has occasionally played a magician character (often as himself) on various television series, such as, \"Magic\", \"The Art of Magic\", \"Something Strange with Max Maven\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Something Strange with Max Maven|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0227951/|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>, and \"The MAXimum Dimension\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxmaven.com/MAXimum.php|title=MAXimum Dimension|accessdate=31 October 2011}}</ref> He has appeared in television series in Sweden, Norway, Finland, Taiwan, England, Canada, Spain, Portugal, and Chile.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sleightsofmind.com/|title=Sleights of Mind \u00bb Magic Advisors|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mspentertainmentagency.com/maxmaven|title=Max Maven - Entertainment Booking Agency|website=mspentertainmentagency.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nMaven has appeared as a part of the traveling science exhibit called \"Magic: The Science of Illusion\" and the \"Magic of the Mind Illusion,\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.maxmaven.com/max.php|title=All About Max ~ MaxMaven.com|website=www.maxmaven.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> which has toured in science museums such as Los Angeles and Boston.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.magicexhibit.org/illusions/illusions_MM.html|title=Magic:The Science of Illusion|accessdate=31 October 2011}}</ref> He has performed often in [[Japan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themagiccafe.com/forums/viewtopic.php?topic=114373&forum=160|title=Magic Cafe|accessdate=31 October 2011}}</ref> and speaks Japanese.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-06-24-ca-8136-story.html|title=Insight From Maven of the Mind : Stage: The mentalist, who will perform in Santa Ana, says he gets hints from body language.|date=1994-06-24|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe has been a frequent speaker at the [[EG Conference]] on creativity and innovation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.egconf.com/presenters/max-maven|title=Max Maven|date=2014-04-07|website=EG Conference|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.egconf.com/videos/max-maven-mystery-theorist-magician-eg8|title=Max Maven, Mystery Theorist & Magician (EG8)|date=2015-11-06|website=EG Conference|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe hosted a 12-part series for [[ITV Wales & West|HTV (Harlech Television)]] in Britain, \"Something Strange with Max Maven,\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Something Strange with Max Maven|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0227951/|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> a talk-show exploring all aspects of the paranormal. The show set a ratings record, and led to a second series the following year. He also starred as the title role in [[Fox Broadcasting Company|FOX]]'s 1992 Halloween special ''Count DeClues' Mystery Castle''<ref>{{Citation|title=Count DeClues' Mystery Castle|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0770733/|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. His performed his interactive magic on [[The World's Greatest Magic]], NBC's highest rated special of 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mspentertainmentagency.com/maxmaven|title=Max Maven - Entertainment Booking Agency|website=mspentertainmentagency.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> \n\nHe hosted his own show on [[Israel]]'s [[Channel 2 (Israeli TV channel)|Channel 2]], a licensed version of ''[[Penn & Teller: Fool Us]]'' called ''Mi Yapil Et Ha Master'' (\"Who Can Fool The Master?)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://itricks.com/news/2017/06/max-maven-fool-me/|title=iTricks.com Magic News, Magic Videos and Podcasts \u00bb Blog Archive \u00bb Max Maven: Fool Me?|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>. And he was a judge for a number of episodes of the 2008 TV [[reality tv]] series [[Celebracadabra]]. <ref>{{Citation|title=Celebracadabra|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1173669/|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\nHe appeared in [[Sitcom]]<nowiki/>s and TV dramas, including as \"The Great Mentos\" in the 1995 [[Fresh Prince of Bel Air]] episode \"Save the Last Trance for Me,\" the 1982 episode of [[Mork & Mindy]] entitled \"Drive, She Said,\" and episodes of [[General Hospital]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0561364/|title=Max Maven|website=IMDb|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.belenzon.com/talent/max-maven/|title=Max Maven - David Belenzon Management, Inc - Max Maven|website=David Belenzon Management, Inc.|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and [[Top Chef]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2009/07/09/top-chef-masters-neil-patrick-harris/|title='Top Chef Masters': Neil Patrick Harris masters another TV genre|website=EW.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>.\n\nIn 2019, he appeared on screen in the documentary about [[The Amazing Johnathan]] directed by Ben Berman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/movies/story/2019-08-14/amazing-johnathan-documentary-magic|title=Review: \u2018The Amazing Johnathan Documentary\u2019 profiles irascible magician in an illusory way|date=2019-08-15|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> and was interviewed<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/food/story/2019-07-24/magic-castle-hollywood-new-chef|title=And for the Magic Castle's next trick: Food that\u2019s worth talking about|date=2019-07-25|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> by the [[Los Angeles Times]] about recent developments at [[The Magic Castle]]. \n\nThe well-reviewed<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://magicreviewed.com/reviews/donna-zuckerbrot-max-maven-a-fabulous-monster/|title=Donna Zuckerbrot-Max Maven - A Fabulous Monster|website=Magic Reviewed|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> feature documentary entitled ''Max Maven: A Fabulous Monster'' was released about him in 2007<ref>{{Citation|title=Max Maven: A Fabulous Monster|url=https://www.gaia.com/video/max-maven-fabulous-monster|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref> by Reel Time Images. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.reeltimeimages.ca/project/max-maven-a-fabulous-monster/|title=Max Maven: A Fabulous Monster|access-date=August 20, 2019}}</ref> It is available for streaming on Amazon Prime.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Max-Maven-Fabulous-Colm-Feore/dp/B00NTSN8VI|title=Amazon.com: Watch Max Maven: A Fabulous Monster {{!}} Prime Video|website=www.amazon.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and Recognitions ==\nMax Maven has received a number of awards for his creativity and performance, including awards from the [[Society of American Magicians]], [[International Brotherhood of Magicians]], and the [[Academy of Magical Arts]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GdEuf2YJ2SEC&pg=PP28&lpg=PP28&dq=max+maven+awards&source=bl&ots=Lsd58bjBuo&sig=ACfU3U0rzNz5cf0NGWgajTiCzBacDtPv9w&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjAyvHG_pLkAhWXqZ4KHfbRDwI4ChDoATAHegQICRAB#v=onepage&q=max%20maven%20awards&f=false|title=Max Maven, Technical Reviewer|website=books.google.com|access-date=August 20, 2019}}</ref> In addition, he has received the following recognitions:\n\n*[[Academy of Magical Arts]] Lecturer of the Year, 1979{{cn|date=August 2019}}\n*[[Academy of Magical Arts]] Creative Fellowship, 1997{{cn|date=August 2019}}\n*The Magic Woods Award for Best Teaching Video for his mentalism DVD \"Nothing,\" 2007.<ref>{{cite journal|date=March 1981|title=Cover page (Special Max Maven issue)|journal=Genii|volume=45|issue=3|pages=1}}</ref>\n*MINDVention Lifetime Achievement Award, 2015<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themagiccafe.com/forums/viewtopic.php?topic=580200&forum=310|title=The Magic Cafe Forums - Max Maven 2015 Guest of Honor!|website=www.themagiccafe.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*The [[Allan Slaight]] Award for Lifetime Achievement, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.magicana.com/video/max-maven-bank-night|title=Max Maven Bank Night|date=2016-05-02|website=Magicana|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.magicana.com/allan-slaight-award-recipients|title=Allan Slaight Award Recipients|date=2016-06-27|website=Magicana|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n== Selected works ==\n* ''Max Maven's Book of Fortunetelling'' <ref>{{Cite book|title=Max Maven's book of fortunetelling|last=Maven|first=Max|date=1992|publisher=Prentice Hall General Reference|isbn=0135641217|edition=1st|location=New York|oclc=25632502}}</ref>\n* ''VideoMind - Phases 1-3: Mentalism'' (3 volume DVD)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://llpub.com/dvds-c-27/videomind-phase-1-parlor-mentalism-max-maven-dvd-p-1332.html|title=Videomind: Phase 1 - Parlor Mentalism - Max Maven - DVD [v2584] - $29.95 : L&L Publishing, The best in magic dvds, books, props and magician's supplies|website=llpub.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://llpub.com/dvds-c-27/videomind-closeup-mentalism-dvd-2-max-maven-p-1331.html|title=Videomind: Close-Up Mentalism - DVD # 2 - Max Maven [v2583] - $29.95 : L&L Publishing, The best in magic dvds, books, props and magician's supplies|website=llpub.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://llpub.com/dvds-c-27/videomind-stage-mentalism-dvd-3-max-maven-p-1333.html|title=Videomind: Stage Mentalism - DVD # 3 - Max Maven [v2585] - $29.95 : L&L Publishing, The best in magic dvds, books, props and magician's supplies|website=llpub.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*''Prism: The Color Series of Mentalism''<ref>{{Cite book|title=Prism: the color series of mentalism|last=Maven|first=Max|date=2005|publisher=Hermetic Press|isbn=0945296487|location=Seattle, WA|oclc=224853800}}</ref>\n*''Nothing'' (2 DVD Set) <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stevensmagic.global/product/nothing-by-max-maven-2-dvd-set/|title=Nothing by Max Maven (2 DVD Set)|website=Stevens Magic Global|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*''Kayfabe'' (4 DVD Set) <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.penguinmagic.com/p/S24074|title=Kayfabe (4 DVD set) by Max Maven and Luis De Matos - DVD|website=Penguin Magic|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*''Max Maven's Mindgames'' (video)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vhscollector.com/movie/max-mavens-mindgames|title=Max Maven's Mindgames {{!}} VHSCollector.com|website=vhscollector.com|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n*''The New Magic of Japan'' (translator)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanishingincmagic.com/blog/fully-booked-magic-of-japan/|title=Fully Booked {{!}} New Magic of Japan|website=www.vanishingincmagic.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{ reflist }}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|www.maxmaven.com}}\n*{{IMDb name|id=0561364|name=Max Maven}}\n*[https://pointofinquiry.org/2006/01/max_maven_magic_and_skepticism/ Interview with Max Maven]\n\n{{Academy of Magical Arts Lecturer of the Year}}\n{{Academy of Magical Arts Creative Fellowship}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maven, Max}}\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:American magicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mentalists]]\n[[Category:Magic consultants]]\n", "name_user": "Desb42", "label": "safe", "comment": "balance link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_Maven"}
{"title_page": "Equestrian at the 1928 Summer Olympics \u2013 Individual eventing", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Equestrian at the Olympics}}\n{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Individual eventing\n|games = 1928 Summer\n|image = \n|caption = \n|venue = [[Hilversum]]\n|date = \n|competitors = 46\n|nations = 17\n|win_value = \n|gold = [[Charles Pahud de Mortanges]] and Marcroix\n|goldNOC = NED\n|silver = [[Gerard de Kruijff]] and Va-T'en\n|silverNOC = NED\n|bronze = [[Bruno Neumann]] and Ilja\n|bronzeNOC = GER\n|prev= [[Equestrian at the 1924 Summer Olympics \u2013 Individual eventing|1924]]\n|next= [[Equestrian at the 1932 Summer Olympics \u2013 Individual eventing|1932]]\n}}\n{{EquestrianAt1928SummerOlympics}}\n\nThe '''individual eventing''' at the '''[[1928 Summer Olympics]]''' (referred to at the time as the \"competition for the equestrian championship\") took place at [[Hilversum]].  The event consisted of a dressage competition, a jumping competition, and an endurance test.  Scores in each component were added to give a total.\n\nScores from the individual competition were summed to give results in the [[Equestrian at the 1928 Summer Olympics \u2013 Team eventing|team competition]].\n\n==Results==\nSource: Official results;<ref name=overallresults>{{cite web|url=http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1928/1928.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080408184510/http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1928/1928.pdf |url-status=dead |archive-date=8 April 2008 |title=1928 Summer Olympics official report }}</ref> De Wael<ref name=hdw>{{cite web|url=http://users.skynet.be/hermandw/olymp/equ1928.html |title=Equestrianism 1928}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Rider\n!Nation\n!Horse\n!Total Score\n\n|-\n!{{gold01}}\n|align=left|[[Charles Pahud de Mortanges]]||align=left|{{flagIOC|NED|1928 Summer}}||align=left|Marcroix\n|1969.82\n|-\n!{{silver02}}\n|